    "recap_headline": "Bowling Green State University Athletics",
    "recap_text": "OXFORD, Ohio\n\u2013\nThe Bowling Green State University baseball team began the weekend series against Miami (OH) Friday night (March 13) after a couple of wind delays. The RedHawks jumped out early, growing their lead to 8-0, including a five-run fifth. The Falcons attempted a comeback, scoring three in the eighth and two in the ninth, but the effort fell short in the 8-5 final score. Offensively, Bowling Green was paced by a three-run home run from\nVinny Salvione\n. As for the mound,\nCarrson Sova\nlocked down Miami in the later innings, giving up just one run over 3.2 innings of work while striking out seven.\nHOW IT HAPPENED\nMiami (OH) tallied the first runs of the game with a two-run home run in the bottom of the first for a 2-0 lead.\nCarter Mottice\ngot the BGSU offense started with a single to left center to begin the third, the first Falcon hit of the day.\nMiami added to their tally in the fifth inning with five runs to stretch their lead to 7-0. The RedHawks added one in the seventh for an 8-0 score.\nThe Falcons got on the board in the eighth inning.\nGriffin Scheiderer\nsingled to right center with\nSam Seidel\nlater drawing his second walk of the game to put two on for BGSU.\nVinny Salvione\nstepped in and took a payoff pitch to deep left for a three-run home run and an 8-3 score, prompting a RedHawk pitching change.\nIn the ninth,\nAndrew DiLodovico\nsingled to left. With two outs,\nZack Horky\ntripled off the center field wall, scoring DiLodovico. A wild pitch in the next at-bat brought Horky home, cutting the score to 8-5.\nSTAT LEADERS\nJacob Turner\n: 4.0 IP, 4 H, 2 R/ER, 1 K\nCarrson Sova\n: 3.2 IP, 1 H, 1 R/ER, 7 K\nVinny Salvione\n: 1-for-4, 1 HR, 3 RBI, 1 R\nZack Horky\n: 1-for-4, 1 3B, 1 RBI, 1 R\nAndrew DiLodovico\n: 1-for-4, 1 R\nGriffin Scheiderer\n: 1-for-4, 1 R\nAnthony Mitta\n: 1-for-4\nFALCON STAT FACTS\nVinny Salvione's\neighth inning home run marked his team-leading fourth of the season and the first three-run home run of the year for BGSU. Salvione also extended his hitting streak to a now team-leading seven games.\nCarrson Sova\ncame on in relief for the Falcons, tossing 3.2 innings. Sova struck out a season-high seven batters, the third time in his BGSU career with 7+ strikeouts in a game, but the first of three as a reliever.\nIn the ninth inning,\nZack Horky\nhit his second triple of the season and the fourth of his career, leading the team for the season and tied on the active roster for career triples.\nAnthony Mitta\ntallied a hit in the game for the Falcons, giving him a hit in 11 of the last 12 games for the Orange and Brown.\nUP NEXT\nBowling Green and Miami (OH) will continue the series with 1 p.m. starts on both Saturday (March 14) and Sunday (March 15) in Oxford.\nAny schedule changes will be announced on BGSUFalcons.com as well as Twitter/X (@BGSU_Baseball).\nFollow the Falcons\nBe sure to follow the Falcons' baseball team on social media\nTwitter - @BGSU_Athletics and @BGSU_Baseball\nInstagram - 'bgfalcons' and 'bgsu_baseball'\nFacebook - 'BGSU Athletics'\nYouTube - 'Falcons Athletics'"
